oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Framed photograph of Maj. and Dr. William Glassell Somerville
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Dr. Somerville was from Memphis and served at a base hopsital with the A.E.F. A psychiatrist, he wrote a pamplet on shell shock (war neuroses) after the war. He practiced medicine in Memphis and also taught at Columbia Univ.
